    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/1518: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 19, 1918—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6674. For Crosby from Rathbone. Treasury 649. Embassy’s 6272, December 13, 12
                    p.m. [<hi rend="italic">7 p.m.</hi>]. Your 682.<note n="8" xml:id="d454fn8">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_540">p. 540</ref>.</note>
                    First: Treasury not disposed to press France to discuss at this time questions
                    relating to whether and to what extent we will convert our demand loans into
                    long time obligations. Second: Secretary Glass agrees with all the views set
                    forth in Treasury 615,<note n="9" xml:id="d454fn9">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_537">p. 537</ref>.</note>
                    notwithstanding paragraphs second and fourth of your 682.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
